e version of the CLI that created this session\\n    38→\\tCLIVersion string `json:\\\"cli_version,omitempty\\\"`\\n    39→\\n    40→\\t// BaseCommit tracks the current shadow branch base. Initially set to HEAD when the\\n    41→\\t// session starts, but updated on migration (pull/rebase) and after condensation.\\n    42→\\t// Used for shadow branch naming and checkpoint storage — NOT for attribution.\\n    43→\\tBaseCommit string `json:\\\"base_commit\\\"`\\n    44→\\n    45→\\t// AttributionBaseCommit is the commit used as the reference point for attribution calculations.\\n    46→\\t// Unlike BaseCommit (which tracks the shadow branch and moves with migration), this field\\n    47→\\t// preserves the original base commit so deferred condensation can correctly calculate\\n    48→\\t// agent vs human line attribution. Updated only after successful condensation.\\n    49→\\tAttributionBaseCommit string `json:\\\"attribution_base_commit,omitempty\\\"`\\n    50→\\n    51→\\t// WorktreePath is the absolute path to the worktree root\\n    52→\\tWorktreePath string `json:\\\"worktree_path,omitempty\\\"`\\n    53→\\n    54→\\t// WorktreeID is the internal git worktree identifier (empty for main worktree)\\n    55→\\t// Derived from .git/worktrees/<name>/, stable across git worktree move\\n    56→\\tWorktreeID string `json:\\\"worktree_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n    57→\\n    58→\\t// StartedAt is when the session was started\\n    59→\\tStartedAt time.Time `json:\\\"started_at\\\"`\\n    60→\\n    61→\\t// EndedAt is when the session was explicitly closed by the user.\\n    62→\\t// nil means the session is still active or was not cleanly closed.\\n    63→\\tEndedAt *time.Time `json:\\\"ended_at,omitempty\\\"`\\n    64→\\n    65→\\t// Phase is the lifecycle stage of this session (see phase.go).\\n    66→\\t// Empty means idle (backward compat with pre-state-machine files).\\n    67→\\tPhase Phase `json:\\\"phase,omitempty\\\"`\\n    68→\\n    69→\\t// TurnID is a unique identifier for the current agent turn.\\n    70→\\t// Lifecycle:\\n    71→\\t//   - Generated fresh in InitializeSession at each turn start\\n    72→\\t//   - Shared across all checkpoints within the same turn\\n    73→\\t//   - Used to correlate related checkpoints when a turn's work spans multiple commits\\n    74→\\t//   - Persists until the next InitializeSession call generates a new one\\n    75→\\tTurnID string `json:\\\"turn_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n    76→\\n    77→\\t// TurnCheckpointIDs tracks all checkpoint IDs condensed during the current turn.\\n    78→\\t// Lifecycle:\\n    79→\\t//   - Set in PostCommit when a checkpoint is condensed for an ACTIVE session\\n    80→\\t//   - Consumed in HandleTurnEnd to finalize all checkpoints with the full transcript\\n    81→\\t//   - Cleared in HandleTurnEnd after finalization completes\\n    82→\\t//   - Cleared in InitializeSession when a new prompt starts\\n    83→\\t//   - Cleared when session is reset (ResetSession deletes the state file entirely)\\n    84→\\tTurnCheckpointIDs []string `json:\\\"turn_checkpoint_ids,omitempty\\\"`\\n    85→\\n    86→\\t// LastInteractionTime is updated on every hook invocation.\\n    87→\\t// Used for stale session detection in \\\"entire doctor\\\".\\n    88→\\tLastInteractionTime *time.Time `json:\\\"last_interaction_time,omitempty\\\"`\\n    89→\\n    90→\\t// StepCount is the number of checkpoints/steps created in this session.\\n    91→\\t// JSON tag kept as \\\"checkpoint_count\\\" for backward compatibility with existing state files.\\n    92→\\tStepCount int `json:\\\"checkpoint_count\\\"`\\n    93→\\n    94→\\t// CheckpointTranscriptStart is the transcript line offset where the current\\n    95→\\t// checkpoint cycle began. Set to 0 at session start, updated to current\\n    96→\\t// transcript length after each condensation. Used to scope the transcript\\n    97→\\t// for checkpoint condensation: \\\"everything since last checkpoint\\\".\\n    98→\\tCheckpointTranscriptStart int `